        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 7:10PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 710 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 7 miles west of New Raymer to 12 miles
north of Westplains, or extending from 26 miles north of Fort Morgan
to 15 miles south of Kimball, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northwestern Sterling, Iliff, Peetz, Westplains, Pawnee Pass,
Stoneham, Willard, Logan Corners, North Sterling Reservoir, New
Raymer, Padroni and Buckingham.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
